George C. Johns, Resp’t, v. The Press Publishing Company, App’lt. (New York Superior Court,

General Term,

Filed March 14, 1890.) Appeal from order vacating an order for the examination of the plaintiff before answer. Be Lancey Nicoll, for app’lt; Art&mus B. Smith, for resp’t. Per Curiam.

The facts of this case, and the questions arising thereon, are in all substantial particulars identical with those-passed upon in Roberts v. The Press Publishing Company, decided *23at the present term of court, and for the reasons given in that case the order appealed from should be affirmed, with ten dollars costs and disbursements.

Sedgwick, Oh. J., and Freedman, X, concur.
